# EasySubmit Resume Format (canonical)

**Rules document:** `EASYSUBMIT_RESUME_RULES.md` (repository root)  
**Golden fixtures:** `ATS_Universal_Resume_Template.pdf`, `ATS_Universal_Resume_Template.docx` (repository root)  
**Code constants:** `lib/resume/resumeSpec.ts` — section order, titles, API download paths  
**Server paths:** `lib/resume/resumeFixtures.server.ts` — root fixture file paths

## Section order (fixed — never reorder)

1. Header — Full Name, then `City, State | Phone | Email | LinkedIn URL`
2. Professional Summary — plain paragraph, no bullets
3. Skills — comma/bullet block, omit if empty
4. Professional Experience — reverse chronological; tab-line title + date
5. Education — reverse chronological
6. Optional: Certifications, Projects, Languages — only if content exists

## Hard never list (see rules §8)

No multi-column, tables, text boxes, header/footer fields, images, hidden text, unicode bullets, creative section names, or skill ratings.

## When changing preview or refinery UI

- Import section titles from `RESUME_SECTION_TITLES` in `lib/resume/resumeSpec.ts`
- Match `PrimeResume` section order to `RESUME_SECTION_ORDER`
- Parser changes: validate against root `ATS_Universal_Resume_Template.pdf` (`npm run validate:ats-template`)
